	<p>Construction of the stadium «Arena Lviv» lasted from 2008-2011. Its construction cost 375 million dollars, and the resulting stadium holds 34,915 spectators. It is the fourth-largest stadium in Ukraine and the one with the most well-lit and visible field of play. The main achievement of this stadium is the very fact of its completion, but there was a lack of conceptual decision-making around its building.</p>
	<p>The stadium is located outside Lviv. It is close to the Stryiskyi bus station and the shopping center «King’s Cross.» The stadium was designed as a key element in the development of the micro region of Sykhiv. However, it is apparent now that the largest problem is the lack of infrastructure: from the stadium to the closest public transport stop is 1.5 km, and there is no direct link to the stadium from the city in Sykhiv at all.  So it is currently unknown how this building will become a part of the everyday life of Lviv’s inhabitants after the tournament.</p>
	<p>After the end of EURO-2012 the stadium will also face the question of its occupancy. Right now there is no clear strategy for use of Arena Lviv, aside from mass events and football matches of the Karparty club, for whom the stadium will be home. There are only broad outlines of a plan for its use, which include a weekly market close to the stadium intended to attract locals, and building on the territory of the stadium parking lot the largest Karting Park in Western Ukraine. The promotion of the stadium will be managed by a specially-created commercial department.</p>

	
